  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Grate approx. 250g <span class=\"text-danger\">[500g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>red cabbage</strong>, discarding the tough&nbsp;stem</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>grated cabbage</strong>&nbsp;to a very large bowl with the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside until later to pickle slightly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chickpeas</strong> to a baking tray with the<strong> ras el hanout</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong>&nbsp;(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and crispy &ndash; these are your <strong>shawarma chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>pitta bread</strong> into rough triangles (pile them up to make it quicker!)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped pitta</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>sumac</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 8-10 min or until golden and crispy &ndash; these are your <strong>sumac pitta chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roughly chop the <strong>dill leaves</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>Greek-style fat-free yoghurt</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and most of the <strong>chopped dill</strong> (save some for garnish!)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up &ndash; this is your <strong>garlic &amp; dill yoghurt</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> roughly</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>grated carrot, baby leaf salad</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>sumac pitta chips</strong> to the <strong>pickled red cabbage</strong> with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up &ndash; this is your <strong>fattoush salad</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/chickpea-shawarma-salad-sumac-pitta-chips/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlic &amp; dill yoghurt</strong> over the <strong>fattoush salad</strong> and top with the <strong>sha</strong><strong><strong>warma</strong> chickpeas</strong></p>\r\n<p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong><strong> dill leaves</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
